<p>In many php frameworks we can do something like:</p>  <pre><code>class Test extends Model {     protected $first;     protected $second;      public function getAllAttributes() {         return $this-&gt;first.','.$this-&gt;second;     } } </code></pre>  <p>How to do this in my own solution? My current model:</p>  <pre><code>class Model {      // ..      public function all() {         return mysqli_query($con, 'select * from '.$this-&gt;table);     }  } </code></pre>  <p>Usage:</p>  <pre><code>$test = new Test(); $result = $test-&gt;all(); foreach ($result as $t) {     echo $t-&gt;getAllAttributes(); } </code></pre>